{"type":"message","id":"a9a56be3","parentId":"6bf57c69","timestamp":"2026-05-08T19:25:07.847Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying that in their experience, Hermes never auto-deletes process messages - they only see OpenClaw do it. The user wants Hermes to auto-delete process messages like \"working...\" \"processing...\" etc., leaving only the final summary/report.\n\nLet me check if Hermes has any settings for this kind of auto-cleanup behavior. Maybe it's a config option or a skill that can enable this.\n\nThe user is not authorizing me to edit anything - they're just asking me to check if it's possible. Let me search more specifically for Hermes auto-cleanup or message pruning settings.\n","thinkingSignature":"9e27a04c4531f31a3886a84f7e1c10eea1fbe8b27ee63d7a227c361160dcdefd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r4m4f3kglxyf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -i \"auto.*delete\\|prune\\|clean\\|process\\|interim\\|preview\\|streaming\" ~/.hermes/config.yaml | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r4m4f3kglxyf_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -i \"delete_orphan\\|hygiene\\|auto_prune\\|prune\" ~/.hermes/config.yaml -A 2 -B 2"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":813,"output":221,"cacheRead":45568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46602,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778268299817,"responseId":"064d6b8e12dbb94bb14a5b9d72986efd"}}
